msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p> 
#. VAR: Ovādavagga → ­bhik­khu­nū­passa­ya­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 23"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "23. Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on nuns’ dwelling places"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.56"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.23.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.276"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="531"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country at Kapilavatthu in "
"the Banyan Tree Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovadanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six went to the nuns’ dwelling "
"place and instructed the nuns from the group of six."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the nuns said to the nuns from the group of six,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“ethāyye, ovādaṃ gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerables, let’s go to the instruction.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Yampi → yaṃ hi (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"“Yampi mayaṃ, ayye, gaccheyyāma ovādassa kāraṇā, ayyā chabbaggiyā idheva "
"āgantvā amhe ovadantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There’s no need; the monks from the group of six came and instructed us "
"right here.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The nuns complained and criticized the monks from the group of six,"

#. VAR: chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti → chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ na gacchissantīti (bj) | chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ­bhik­khu­nū­passa­yaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadantīti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six go and instruct the nuns at their "
"dwelling place?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And those nuns told the monks."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="532"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six go and instruct the nuns at their "
"dwelling place?”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo "
"ovadathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadissatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you go and instruct the nuns at their dwelling place?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.17a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="533"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk goes to a nun’s dwelling place, and then instructs her, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="534"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.23.2"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.277"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="535"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena mahāpajāpati gotamī gilānā hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards Mahāpajāpati Gotamī became sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Therā bhikkhū yena mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "The senior monks went to see her"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavocuṃ—“"
msgstr "and said,"

#. VAR: kacci → kacci te (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "kacci, gotami, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“We hope you’re bearing up, Gotamī, we hope you’re getting better?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "“Na me, ayyā, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ”."
msgstr "“I’m not bearing up, Venerables, and I’m not getting better."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "“Iṅghayyā, dhammaṃ desethā”ti."
msgstr "Please give me a teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.7"
msgid ""
"“Na, bhagini, kappati bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo dhammaṃ "
"desetun”ti kukkuccāyantā na desesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It’s not allowable for us to go and teach a nun at her dwelling place.” And "
"being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach her."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards, the Master robed up in the morning, took his bowl and robe, "
"and went to Mahāpajāpati Gotamī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said to her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "“kacci, gotami, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“I hope you’re bearing up, Gotamī, I hope you’re getting better?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "“Pubbe me, bhante, therā bhikkhū āgantvā dhammaṃ desenti."
msgstr "“Previously, Venerable Sir, the senior monks would come and teach me,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Tena me phāsu hoti."
msgstr "and because of that I would be comfortable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Idāni pana—‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti, kukkuccāyantā na desenti."
msgstr ""
"But now they don’t teach because they’re afraid of wrongdoing, saying, ‘It’s "
"been prohibited by the Master.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Tena me na phāsu hotī”ti."
msgstr "And because of that I’m not comfortable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.16"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā "
"samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"After instructing, inspiring, and gladdening her with a teaching, the Master "
"rose from his seat and departed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.18"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā gilānaṃ bhikkhuniṃ "
"ovadituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to go and instruct a sick nun at her dwelling place."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.57"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="536"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: bhikkhunupassayaṃ → bhik­khu­nū­passa­yaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.20"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, "
"aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk goes to the nuns’ dwelling place and then instructs them, unless "
"there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānā hoti bhikkhunī—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is that a nun is sick.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "(<em>23</em>:<strong>72</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.23.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.23.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="537"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.278"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="538"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunupassayo nāma"
msgstr "The nuns’ dwelling place:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "yattha bhikkhuniyo ekarattampi vasanti."
msgstr "where nuns stay for even a single night."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="539"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvāti"
msgstr "Goes to:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "tattha gantvā."
msgstr "goes there."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="540"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "Them:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "they have been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="541"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Ovadeyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "aṭṭhahi garudhammehi ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he instructs about the eight rules to be respected, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="542"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="543"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "Gilānā nāma"
msgstr "A sick nun:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. A formal meeting of the community,” <i lang="pli">saṃvāsa</i>, is defined at <i lang="pli">pācittiya</i> 69, <ref>MS.2.1274</ref>, as the observance day ceremony, the invitation ceremony, or a procedure.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "bhikkhunī na sakkoti ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā gantuṃ."
msgstr ""
"she is not able to go to the instruction or to a formal meeting of the "
"community."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.23.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="544"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Upasampannāya upasampannasaññī bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra "
"samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is fully ordained, and he perceives her as fully ordained, and he "
"goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Upasampannāya vematiko bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā "
"ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is fully ordained, but he is unsure if she is, and he goes to her "
"dwelling place and then instructs her, unless there is an appropriate "
"reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññī bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra "
"samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is fully ordained, but he perceives her as not fully ordained, and he "
"goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="545"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Aññena dhammena ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs her with another teaching, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is not fully ordained, but he perceives her as fully ordained, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampannāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If she is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If she is not fully ordained, and he perceives her as not fully ordained, "
"there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.23.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="546"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "uddesaṃ dento,"
msgstr "if he gives a summary;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "paripucchaṃ dento,"
msgstr "if he questions them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno osāreti,"
msgstr "if he recites when asked to do so;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "pañhaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,"
msgstr "if he replies when asked a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,"
msgstr ""
"if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is to a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.10"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is to a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="547"></a> 
#. VAR: Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpadaṃ → bhik­khu­nū­passa­ya­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc23:pts-cs3.3.13"
msgid "Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The third rule, the training rule on nuns’ dwelling places, is finished."

